* 2 - Territory: A territory over which a country claims jurisdiction and exists either outside the primary borders of its parent country or of the territorial waters of its parent country.

* 3 - Geographical area: A geographical area over which no country claims jurisdiction and exists outside any country's borders.

* 4 - Disputed territory: A territory over which more than one country claims jurisdiction and where the dispute has not been resolved.

* 1 - Une entrée « Active » sur cette liste correspond au nom valide actuel du pays ou de la zone d'intérêt.

* 2 - Une entrée « Inactive » incluent les pays qui ne sont plus reconnus comme États souverains par le gouvernement canadien (par ex. l'URSS, la Yougoslavie, etc.) ou les anciens noms de pays ou de zones d'intérêt actives (par ex. la Birmanie --> le Myanmar)","type_override":""}},{"id":"STAT_DESC_EN","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Country Status Description","label_fr":"Description du statut du pays (anglais)","notes_en":"Current or historical status of a record.","notes_fr":"Statut actuel ou historique d'une entrée.","type_override":""}},{"id":"STAT_DESC_FR","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Country Status Description (French)","label_fr":"Description du Statut du pays","notes_en":"Current or historical status of a record.","notes_fr":"Statut actuel ou historique d'une entrée.","type_override":""}},{"id":"TYPE_CD","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"GC Country Type Code","label_fr":"GC code du type de pays","notes_en":"Indicates whether the row represents a country, territory, geographical area or disputed territory, or a special case.

There are 6 possible values for this row:

* 1 - Country: A country (nation state) that has jurisdiction over itself. In ISO terms, this is either a UN Member State or a UN Observer State. It may also be a country recognized by Canada but NOT recognized by the UN nor ISO.

* 2 - Territory: A territory over which a country claims jurisdiction and exists either outside the primary borders of its parent country or of the territorial waters of its parent country.

* 3 - Geographical area: A geographical area over which no country claims jurisdiction and exists outside any country's borders.

* 4 - Disputed territory: A territory over which more than one country claims jurisdiction and where the dispute has not been resolved.

* 5 - Special case: The remarks field will provide additional information to the reader.

* 6 - Non-self-governing Territory: A territory identified by the UN as a non-self-governing territory.","notes_fr":"Un identifiant qui indique si la ligne représente un pays, un territoire, une zone géographique ou un territoire contesté, ou un cas particulier. Un identifiant numérique indiquant si la ligne représente un pays, un territoire, une zone géographique ou un territoire contesté, ou un cas particulier. Il y a 6 valeurs possibles pour cette ligne:

* 1 - Pays: Un pays (État-nation) qui a juridiction sur lui-même. En termes ISO, il s'agit soit d’un État membre de l'ONU ou d’un État observateur de l'ONU. Il peut également s'agir d'un pays reconnu par le Canada mais NON reconnu par l'ONU ni par l'ISO.

* 2 - Territoire: Un territoire sur lequel un pays revendique sa juridiction et qui existe en dehors des principales frontières de son pays d'origine ou des eaux territoriales de son pays d'origine.

* 3 - Zone géographique: Une zone géographique sur laquelle aucun pays ne revendique sa juridiction et qui existe en dehors des frontières de n’importe quel pays.

* 4 - Territoire contesté : Un territoire contesté. Plus d'un pays revendique sa juridiction et le différend n'a pas été résolu

* 5 - Cas particulier : Un cas particulier

* 6 - Territoire non autonome : Un territoire identifié par l'ONU comme territoire non autonome","type_override":""}},{"id":"TYPE_DESC_EN","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Country Type Description","label_fr":"Description du type de pays (anglais)","notes_en":"Indicates whether the row represents a country, territory, geographical area or disputed territory, or a special case.","notes_fr":"Un identifiant qui indique si la ligne représente un pays, un territoire, une zone géographique ou un territoire contesté, ou un cas particulier. Un identifiant numérique indiquant si la ligne représente un pays, un territoire, une zone géographique ou un territoire contesté, ou un cas particulier.","type_override":""}},{"id":"TYPE_DESC_FR","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Country Type Description (French)","label_fr":"Description du type de pays","notes_en":"Indicates whether the row represents a country, territory, geographical area or disputed territory, or a special case.","notes_fr":"Un identifiant qui indique si la ligne représente un pays, un territoire, une zone géographique ou un territoire contesté, ou un cas particulier. Un identifiant numérique indiquant si la ligne représente un pays, un territoire, une zone géographique ou un territoire contesté, ou un cas particulier.","type_override":""}},{"id":"RECENT_IND","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Latest value indicator","label_fr":"Dernière valeur (indicateur)","notes_en":"Indicates the latest value of a country's information, including countries or territories that are no longer active (such as the former Yugoslavia). ","type_override":""}},{"id":"EFF_DT","type":"timestamp","info":{"label_en":"Effective Date","label_fr":"Date effective","notes_en":"Period of validity (start date) of the name of a country or area of interest, as of the time this name was recognised by the government of Canada. (*Notez que la date de fin est fixée à 2100 lorsque le nom du pays ou de la zone d'intérêt est toujours courante). ","type_override":"timestamp"}},{"id":"OBSERVATIONS_EN","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Observations","label_fr":"Observations (anglais)","notes_en":"English observations by data steward.","notes_fr":"Observations en anglais par responsable des données.","type_override":""}},{"id":"OBSERVATIONS_FR","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Observations (French)","label_fr":"Observations","notes_en":"French observations by data steward.","notes_fr":"Observations en français par responsable des données.","type_override":""}},{"id":"GC_PAR_ID","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Parent country ID","label_fr":"Pays parent ID","notes_en":"The GC_ID of the geographic entity from which this country or area of interest originated, through seceding from, or dissolution of a country or area of interest.","notes_fr":"Le GC_ID de l'entité géographique d'où est originaire ce pays ou cette zone d'intérêt, par sécession ou dissolution d'un pays ou d'une zone d'intérêt.","type_override":""}},{"id":"GC_JUR_ID","type":"text","info":{"label_en":"Administrative Jurisdiction ID","label_fr":"Jurisdiction administrative ID","notes_en":"The GC_ID of the country that has administrative jurisdiction over the territory. Only rows where the GC Country Type code is 'Territory' (2) and the GC Country Status Code is 'Active' (1) will have a value. If there is no value, that means:  

1) it's a country 

2) it's a geographical area and there is no country that claims jurisdiction 

3) it's a territory that has expired 

4) it's an area where there is a dispute or a special case (from Canada's perspective). The dispute may involve the countries that claim jurisdiction over the area, or the dispute may involve the nature of the area itself (is it a country or a territory). 

When a value is assigned it must reference an existing GC_ID where the TYPE_CD is 1.","notes_fr":"Le GC_ID du pays qui a la juridiction administrative sur le territoire. Seules les lignes où le code de type de pays GC est « Territoire » (2) et le code de statut de pays GC est « Actif » (1) auront une valeur. S'il n'y a pas de valeur, cela signifie que : 

1) C'est un pays

* 2 - Territory: A territory over which a country claims jurisdiction and exists either outside the primary borders of its parent country or of the territorial waters of its parent country.

* 3 - Geographical area: A geographical area over which no country claims jurisdiction and exists outside any country's borders.

* 4 - Disputed territory: A territory over which more than one country claims jurisdiction and where the dispute has not been resolved.

* 2 - Territoire: Un territoire sur lequel un pays revendique sa juridiction et qui existe en dehors des principales frontières de son pays d'origine ou des eaux territoriales de son pays d'origine.

* 3 - Zone géographique: Une zone géographique sur laquelle aucun pays ne revendique sa juridiction et qui existe en dehors des frontières de n’importe quel pays.

author Patrick Little <patrick.little@tbs-sct.gc.ca> 1735228790 -0500
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1735228790 -0500

Create usage.yml

files.patch:
@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@
+name: Update usage
+
+on:
+  schedule:
+    - cron: "10 6 * * *" # Runs daily at midnight UTC
+  workflow_dispatch: # Allow manual triggering of the workflow
+
+jobs:
+  update-dashboard:
+    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
+
+    steps:
+      - name: Checkout repository
+        uses: actions/checkout@v3
+
+      - name: Set up Python
+        uses: actions/setup-python@v4
+        with:
+          python-version: "3.x"
+
+      - name: Install dependencies
+        run: |
+          python -m pip install --upgrade pip
+          pip install ckanapi
+
+      - name: Run Usage Fetcher
+        run: python portal_usage_fetcher.py
+
+      - name: Commit and Push Usage Results
+        env:
+          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
+        run: |
+          git add -A
+          git commit --allow-empty -m "Update usage data" || echo "No changes to commit"
+          git push

Create big_things.yml

files.patch:
@@ -0,0 +1,172 @@
+name: Scrape Website
+
+on:
+  schedule:
+    - cron: '0 12,16,21,4 * * *'  # 12 PM, 4 PM, 9 PM, 4 AM UTC
+  workflow_dispatch:  # Allows manual triggering of the workflow
+
+permissions:
+  contents: write
+  issues: write
+
+jobs:
+  setup:
+    name: Setup Environment
+    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
+    steps:
+    - name: Checkout repository
+      uses: actions/checkout@v3
+
+    - name: Configure Git
+      run: |
+        git config --global user.email "your-email@example.com"
+        git config --global user.name "Your Name"
+
+    - name: Set up Python
+      uses: actions/setup-python@v4
+      with:
+        python-version: '3.x'
+
+    - name: Install Python Dependencies
+      run: |
+        python -m pip install --upgrade pip
+        pip install requests beautifulsoup4 ckanapi markdownify
+
+    - name: Install Node.js
+      uses: actions/setup-node@v3
+      with:
+        node-version: '18'
+
+    - name: Install Puppeteer
+      run: npm install puppeteer node-fetch@2
+
+  scrape:
+    name: Scrape Data
+    needs: setup
+    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
+    steps:
+    - name: Run scraper
+      run: python scraper.py
+
+    - name: Run REF_STDs scraper
+      run: python REF_STDs/scraper.py
+
+    - name: Commit and Push Scraped Data
+      env:
+        GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
+      run: |
+        git add docs/scraped_table_en.csv docs/scraped_table_fr.csv docs/scraped_content_eng.html docs/scraped_content_fra.html *.atom REF_STDs/
+        git commit -m "Update scraped data and content"
+        git push
+      continue-on-error: true
+
+  detect_changes:
+    name: Detect Changes
+    needs: scrape
+    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
+    steps:
+    - name: Check Commit Message
+      id: check_commit_message
+      run: |
+        COMMIT_MESSAGE=$(git log -1 --pretty=%B)
+        echo "Last commit message: $COMMIT_MESSAGE"
+        if [[ "$COMMIT_MESSAGE" == *"Update scraped data and content"* ]]; then
+          echo "changed=true" >> $GITHUB_ENV
+        else
+          echo "changed=false" >> $GITHUB_ENV
+
+    - name: Take Screenshots if Changes Detected
+      if: env.changed == 'true'
+      run: |
+        node -e "
+        const puppeteer = require('puppeteer');
+        (async () => {
+          const browser = await puppeteer.launch();
+          const page = await browser.newPage();
+          await page.goto('https://www.canada.ca/en/government/system/digital-government/digital-government-innovations/enabling-interoperability/gc-enterprise-data-reference-standards.html');
+          await page.screenshot({ path: 'docs/screenshot_en.png', fullPage: true, captureBeyondViewport: true });
+          await page.goto('https://www.canada.ca/fr/gouvernement/systeme/gouvernement-numerique/innovations-gouvernementales-numeriques/permettre-interoperabilite/normes-referentielles-pangouvernementales-relatives-donnees-gc.html');
+          await page.screenshot({ path: 'docs/screenshot_fr.png', fullPage: true, captureBeyondViewport: true });
+          await browser.close();
+        })();
+        "
+
+    - name: Commit and Push Screenshots
+      if: env.changed == 'true'
+      run: |
+        git add docs/screenshot_en.png docs/screenshot_fr.png
+        git commit -m "Add updated screenshots for data change detection"
+        git push
+      continue-on-error: true
+
+  create_issue:
+    name: Create GitHub Issue
+    needs: detect_changes
+    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
+    if: env.changed == 'true'
+    steps:
+    - name: Create Issue Body
+      run: |
+        echo "# Data Change Detected" > issue_body.md
+        git log --stat --pretty=fuller HEAD~2..HEAD > issue_body.md
+        echo "The data on the monitored website has changed. The screenshots of the updated pages are attached below." >> issue_body.md
+        echo "![Screenshot EN](https://github.com/PatLittle/GC-Ref-Data-Tracker/blob/main/docs/screenshot_en.png?raw=true)" >> issue_body.md
+        echo "![Screenshot FR](https://github.com/PatLittle/GC-Ref-Data-Tracker/blob/main/docs/screenshot_fr.png?raw=true)" >> issue_body.md
+
+    - name: Create Issue
+      uses: peter-evans/create-issue-from-file@v4
+      with:
+        title: "Data Change Detected on Website"
+        content-filepath: issue_body.md
+        labels: update, screenshot
+        assignees: your-github-username
+
+  fetch_feeds:
+    name: Fetch Feeds
+    needs: scrape
+    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
+    steps:
+    - name: Run Feed Fetcher
+      run: |
+        python atom_feed_fetcher.py
+        python portal_usage_fetcher.py
+      continue-on-error: true
+
+    - name: Commit and Push Feed Results
+      run: |
+        git add -A
+        git commit --allow-empty -m "Update fetched feeds"
+        git push
+      continue-on-error: true
+
+  fetch_usage:
+    name: Fetch usage
+    needs: scrape
+    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
+    steps:
+    - name: Run usage Fetcher
+      run: |
+        python portal_usage_fetcher.py
+      continue-on-error: true
+
+    - name: Commit and Push Feed Results
+      run: |
+        git add -A
+        git commit --allow-empty -m "Update fetched feeds"
+        git push

+def fetch_and_save_ratings(resource_id, output_file):
+    try:
+        result = rc.action.datastore_search(
+            resource_id=resource_id,
+            filters={"uuid": dataset_ids},
+        )
+        
+        with open(output_file, "w") as json_file:
+            json.dump(result, json_file)
+
+        print(f"Data from resource_id {resource_id} saved to {output_file}")
+
+    except Exception as e:
+        print(f"Error fetching data for resource_id {resource_id}: {e}")
